headline: New TI MCUs enable edge AI and industry-leading real-time control to advance system efficiency, safety and sustainability
summary: Texas Instruments (TI) (Nasdaq: TXN) today introduced two new series of real-time microcontrollers that deliver advancements to help engineers achieve more intelligent and secure processing in automotive and industrial applications. TI's TMS320F28P55x series of C2000™ MCUs is the industry's first portfolio of real-time microcontrollers with an integrated neural processing unit (NPU), enabling fault detections with high accuracy and low latency. The F29H85x series is built on TI's new 64-bit C29
